==English==
===Etymology===
From medieval Latin ''[[actuatus]]'', past participle of ''[[actuare]]'', from ''[[actus]]'' "act".

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|actuat|e|}}
# {{transitive}} To [[activate]], or put something into [[motion]]; to [[animate]].
# {{transitive}} To [[incite]] someone to [[action]]; to [[motivate]].

